## Tradeoffs

<!--
What does this perspective give up? Every strong position has costs.
Naming them here is what distinguishes a perspective from a sales
pitch — and gives the synthesiser the data it needs to weigh this
voice against the others.

Cover at minimum:
  - What this approach is bad at
  - What it assumes about the environment / user / future
  - What it would cost (time, money, complexity, ongoing maintenance)
  - What classes of failure it does not address
-->

- **Gives up**: (what capability or property this approach sacrifices)
- **Assumes**: (preconditions that, if violated, invalidate the claim)
- **Costs**: (concrete resources — hours, dollars, cognitive load)
- **Does not address**: (problems adjacent to {{TOPIC}} this angle ignores)

